Echo server in 10-years old Tcl (more?):<p><pre><code>    socket -server acceptConnections 9999
    proc acceptConnections {fd clientaddr clientport} {
        fconfigure $fd -blocking 0
        fileevent $fd readable [list replyToClient $fd]
    }
    proc replyToClient fd {
        set s [read $fd]
        puts -nonewline $fd $s
        flush $fd
    }
    vwait forever
</code></pre>
Note that this is a multiplexing non blocking server, exactly like Twisted / Tornado. All features built-in in the language. Tcl failed copying the obvious missing features from other languages. Other languages are failing copying the good things from Tcl.<p>p.s. note the poetry contained in the "vwait forever" statement ;) Our program is willing to run without stop until the end of the universe.
